cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and image processing, specifically color constancy. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper provides guidelines for supervised methods, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The data set also includes images taken by a mobile camera, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the spectral responses of cameras and light sources, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics).
